channel.title: Jagex cache
channel.description: Well i have been wondering....how do you access/view the current jagex cache? (if it's possible)

item.title: Jagex cache
item.dc:creator: @system system
item.description:
@system wrote:

[quote=“Primadude, post:12, topic:328584”][quote author=Jamie1200 link=topic=424970.msg3121751#msg3121751 date=1265579378]

Let RuneScape fully load and update close that window and then find the cache in your c drive (should be in c drive, your account, or the windows folder.) then use a cache unpacker on it. Keep on trying to get it until you find the sprites part. JagEx has a habit of hiding their files.

I unpacked it but it has everything but sprites >.>

I’m sure Jagex found a way to hide their sprites elsewhere.

Like not in your PC.
[/quote]

Are you stupid? Of course they have the sprites in the cache, which is situated in anyone’s PC who has played RS.[/quote]

Dickatron 3000?

Read full topic
